# Methodology
methodology       : subprocess-per-cell, nvidia-smi memory.used polling
sampler           : background thread, 30 ms interval
child_hold_ms     : 800 (post-READY steady-state window)
warmup            : 500 ms settle before baseline sample
strip_h_body      : 256 (matches CHANGELOG P2.7 reference 4096² number)
synth_pair        : deterministic offset distortion ((x*17 + y*5) % 251)
backend           : CUDA (cubecl::cuda::CudaRuntime)
build             : --release --features cuda
binary            : target/release/gpu-vram-profile
harness           : benchmarks/heaptrack/drivers/gpu_vram_profile/src/main.rs

# What's measured
metric            : peak `nvidia-smi --query-gpu=memory.used` - baseline
                    during one `compute_dkl_jod()` call (or
                    `warm_reference + compute_dkl_jod_with_warm_ref`
                    for Mode E strip).
estimator_bytes   : output of cvvdp_gpu::estimate_gpu_memory_bytes*
                    (analytical pipeline estimator, does NOT include
                    cubecl pool over-allocation or driver page rounding).

# Cells
n_cells           : 16
sizes_swept       : 1024² (1.05 MP), 2048² (4.19 MP), 2896² (8.39 MP),
                    4096² (16.78 MP), 7680×5184 (39.81 MP stretch)
modes_swept       : full, strip (Mode E warm-ref path), strip_pair
                    (Mode B), capped_pyramid5

# Calibration vs CHANGELOG.md:1361-1363 P2.7 partial
calibration_target_4096sq_modeB_mib : 1502
calibration_measured_4096sq_modeB_mib: 2273
calibration_status   : DIVERGENT (+771 MiB above CHANGELOG target)
calibration_root_cause: The "Path B unfix (2026-05-27)" commit after
                        P2.7 added a persistent `DBandsTransient`
                        sized at base-level n0 = width × height to
                        eliminate per-band `alloc_zeros_f32` calls
                        (208 zero-upload HtoDs at 4096²). At 4096²,
                        5 buffer kinds × 3 channels × 16 MP × 4 bytes
                        = 960 MiB returned to the persistent working
                        set. The CHANGELOG's 1502 MiB number was
                        measured BEFORE this unfix; current master is
                        2273 MiB on the same code path. See
                        `crates/cvvdp-gpu/src/pipeline.rs:925-957`
                        (the `d_bands_transient` field doc) for the
                        wall-time-vs-peak-memory tradeoff rationale.
verification         : cross-checked with
                       `cargo run --release --example mem_mode_b_vs_full -p cvvdp-gpu --features cuda`
                       on the same commit → 4096² Mode B nvsmi delta
                       2274 MiB (matches gpu-vram-profile within 1 MiB,
                       confirming the harness is calibrated against
                       the reference example and the divergence from
                       CHANGELOG is a real source-level change, not
                       a methodology artifact).

# Estimator-vs-runtime gap (per cell, MiB)
# Computed in TSV column `runtime_vs_estimator_bytes`.
# At 4096² Full: runtime delta 3969 MiB vs estimator 2859 MiB → +1110 MiB pool overhead
# At 4096² Mode B: runtime delta 2273 MiB vs estimator 565 MiB → +1708 MiB pool overhead
# The Mode B estimator is even more optimistic than the Full estimator
# because it models the post-P2.7-FULL design target (where gauss_ref
# and gauss_alt would also be strip-shaped at shallow levels). The
# Path B unfix did not touch the estimator, so the gap to runtime
# widened with the unfix.

