# 40 MP stretch — did NOT OOM
40mp_full_status            : OK (delta 7362 MiB, peak 9083 MiB on
                              12 GB RTX 5070 — 75% full)
40mp_modeB_status           : OK (delta 5153 MiB, peak 6875 MiB)
40mp_observation            : Full at 40 MP fits with 3 GiB headroom
                              on RTX 5070; Mode B leaves 5 GiB headroom.
                              An 8 GB card would OOM Full at 40 MP
                              but tolerate Mode B.

# wgpu backend status
wgpu_backend_tested         : NO — cubecl-wgpu build adds ~5 min and
                              wgpu can't probe nvsmi memory the same
                              way (NVIDIA wgpu sits below the CUDA
                              driver, so memory.used will still report
                              CUDA-context bytes, not pure wgpu
                              allocations, on this NVIDIA host). The
                              CUDA backend is what production hits;
                              that's what we measure here.
